pullsbody:
This consumes the new id_token claims from https://github.com/mozilla/fxa-oauth-server/pull/530 to determine whether the user signed in with 2FA, and if they did so, displays a nice little :lock: icon next to their email address.

The bulk of the change here is actually in the second commit, which makes the OAuth flow use [/.well-known/openid-configuration](https://accounts.firefox.com/.well-known/openid-configuration) and consume the OpenID Connect id_token.  The actual figuring-out-2fa-status part them just becomes a matter of looking for the "acr" claim in the id_token.

@vladikoff this :lock: business is mostly for my own demo purposes, but what do you think about merging at least the OIDC refactor stuff back to mainline?  I think it's a nice cleanup overall, but I might have unintentionally broken something else that this repo was doing.

